properties.areaDesc: Mississippi Sound; South Mobile Bay; North Mobile Bay
properties.headline: Dense Fog Advisory issued January 10 at 2:17PM CST until January 11 at 10:00AM CST by NWS Mobile AL
properties.description:
* WHAT...For the Dense Fog Advisory, dense fog will reduce
visibility to 1 mile or less. For the Small Craft Advisory,
southeast winds 15 to 25 kt with gusts up to 35 kt.

* WHERE...Northern Mobile Bay, Southern Mobile Bay and
Mississippi Sound.

* WHEN...For the Dense Fog Advisory, from 6 PM this evening to
10 AM CST Saturday. For the Small Craft Advisory, until 6 PM
CST Saturday.

* IMPACTS...Conditions will be hazardous to small craft. Low
visibility will make navigation difficult.
properties.instruction:
Inexperienced mariners, especially those operating smaller
vessels, should avoid navigating in hazardous conditions.

If you must navigate, proceed with caution. Use proper fog
signals. Make sure all running lights are on. Remember to use
your radar and compass.

NWSheadline: SMALL CRAFT ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 6 PM CST SATURDAY... ...DENSE FOG ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 6 PM THIS EVENING TO 10 AM CST SATURDAY
